{"summary":"All four amendments have technical merit. Three address concrete correctness bugs in ambiguous lineage updates, duplicate run reporting, and journal repair drift; the remaining one is smaller but still usefully documents a real hidden parser invariant.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-9-f0ca9b46","decision":"accept","rationale":"Both sites independently serialize the same journal-details wire format, and `append_event_if_missing` relies on being able to parse the service-produced string and re-render it for repair. Leaving two implementations invites silent drift that turns replay/backfill from an in-place repair into a duplicate append, so consolidating the formatter improves correctness and maintainability."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-1fa4f2f8","decision":"accept","rationale":"`CompletionJournalDetails::parse()` has an implicit invariant that only the trailing `detail` field may contain `\", \"`; `project_id`, `run_id`, and `plan_hash` are parsed as delimiter-free identifiers. That assumption is not obvious from the code and is not enforced by the identifier types, so documenting it with a comment or `debug_assert!` is a sound hardening step even if a future structured encoding would be stronger."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-f4e1cccb","decision":"accept","rationale":"When an explicit `run_id` has no exact match, the current fallback can finalize a lone runless running row without accounting for other still-running rows for the same bead/project. In a mixed `[run_id=None] + [run_id=run-2]` state, finalizing `run-3` is not a safe unique match; it guesses which corrupted row to rewrite and violates the documented requirement to reject ambiguous updates."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-6ff93073","decision":"accept","rationale":"`collapse_task_run_attempts()` currently normalizes legacy start+terminal pairs but leaves repeated terminal rows for the same attempt intact. That means `find_runs_for_bead()` can overcount retries and outcomes when NDJSON contains replayed duplicate completions, which is a real correctness bug for the audit/query path and should be deduplicated defensively."}]}